<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Embark" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Embark,</orth> 1) trans. a) to put on shipboard: <bibl n="shak. err 5.409" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 409</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III Chor.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.3.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 3, 1</bibl>. -- b) to engage: <cit><quote>he's --ed to the Cyprus wars,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 1.1.150" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 1, 150</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) intr. to go on shipboard: <cit><quote>to e. for Milan,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 1.1.71" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. I, 1, 71</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the --ed traders,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.127" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 127</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>was --ed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.10" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 10</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he --ed at Milford,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 3.6.62" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 6, 62</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.4.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 4, 27</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>